
'''= Matthias Kroner [http://www.fidor.de/] talks about a new kind of community bank.'''


=Description=

"he questions the classical model of risk averse, product led banks. He offers an alternative view that positions the bank as open as in open source, community driven, with no sale people but a reputation based on the reputation of the people who use the service. It’s a stunning vision of what a bank could look like in the post financial crisis period."
